H0.text: What name is given to the gap between the A and B rings of Saturn, after the Italian astronomer who first discovered it in 1675. Cassini Division

H1.text: What name is given to the gap between the A and B rings of Saturn, after the Italian astronomer who first discovered it in 1675. Encke Gap

H2.text: What name is given to the gap between the A and B rings of Saturn, after the Italian astronomer who first discovered it in 1675. Huygens Gap

H3.text: What name is given to the gap between the A and B rings of Saturn, after the Italian astronomer who first discovered it in 1675. F Ring

A4.text: The Cassini Division is a 4,800-kilometre-wide (3,000 mi) region between the A ring and B Ring.

A5.text: The Encke Gap is a 325-km (200 mile) wide gap within the A ring, centered at a distance of 133,590 km (83,000 miles) from Saturn's center.
